TrustForge is an open identity, capability, and proof protocol for
humans, devices, agents, services, and packets. This pfSense package
installs the reference daemon (tf-daemon), an rc.d service script, a
web UI under Services > TrustForge, and a sample configuration.

The daemon supports both live authenticated sessions and standalone
signed/encrypted packets, and can act as a relay node in mesh / LoRa /
air-gapped deployments. On pfSense it is most commonly enabled as the
"tf-home-compatible" or "tf-enterprise-edge" profile.

WWW: https://github.com/trustforge/trustforge
